			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Recycling metal items from your household is an excellent way to save energy and help reduce overall waste. In fact, recycling metals produces the largest energy savings of any other material. The process of recycling compared with the process of producing aluminium, lead and steel requires 94 percent, 75 percent and 72 percent less energy respectively. Recycled steel scrap is a low-emitting source of the metal - but the majority of available material is already collected. Further optimizing steel scrap recovery will be crucial in decarbonizing steel production.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">回收利用家中的金属物品是节约能源和帮助减少整体浪费的绝佳方式。事实上，回收金属比其他任何材料都能节省大量能源。与铝、铅和钢的生产过程相比，回收过程所需的能源分别减少 94%、75% 和 72%。回收的废钢是一种低排放的金属来源，但大部分可用材料已经被收集起来。进一步优化废钢回收对钢铁生产的脱碳至关重要。</common:generalComment>
